abstract: The former New York City mayor submitted paperwork to enter the presidential primary in Alabama, which has the first filing deadline, indicating he would pursue a risky strategy of skipping all four traditional early-state contests.
snippet: The former New York City mayor submitted paperwork to enter the presidential primary in Alabama, which has the first filing deadline, indicating he would pursue a risky strategy of skipping all four traditional early-state contests.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg disrupted the Democratic presidential field on Friday as he took his first steps into the 2020 race, unnerving supporters of Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and prompting Senators Elizabeth Warren and Bernie Sanders to accuse Mr. Bloomberg of seeking to buy the presidency.

headline_main: DealBook: U.S. and China Could Roll Back Tariffs

abstract: Bill Gates and others warn that higher taxes would lead to lower growth. They have their facts backward.
snippet: Bill Gates and others warn that higher taxes would lead to lower growth. They have their facts backward.
lead_paragraph: When Bill Gates founded Microsoft in 1975, the top marginal tax rate on personal income was 70 percent, tax rates on capital gains and corporate income were significantly higher than at present, and the estate tax was a much more formidable levy. None of that dissuaded Mr. Gates from pouring himself into his business, nor discouraged his investors from pouring in their money.

abstract: A New York Times/Siena College survey in six key states also showed voters want a candidate who can work with Republicans.
snippet: A New York Times/Siena College survey in six key states also showed voters want a candidate who can work with Republicans.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats in the country’s most pivotal general election battlegrounds prefer a moderate presidential nominee who would seek common ground with Republicans rather than pursue an ambitious, progressive agenda, according to a New York Times/Siena College poll of primary voters across six states.

abstract: Bernie Sanders has raised more money from Latino donors than any of his Democratic rivals and he leads the field with Latino support in a new poll.
snippet: Bernie Sanders has raised more money from Latino donors than any of his Democratic rivals and he leads the field with Latino support in a new poll.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Three months before anyone starts voting in the Democratic primaries, advisers for Bernie Sanders are confident about the new voters they are registering in Iowa. They expect a decisive victory in New Hampshire, where Mr. Sanders, the senator from neighboring Vermont, is seen as a local. And in California, a state the campaign views as clearing a path to the nomination, they believe Mr. Sanders has a clear advantage with the not-so-secret weapon of Latino voters.

abstract: The testimony seemed to bolster the prosecution’s contention that Roger Stone, an ex-Trump campaign aide, deliberately lied to congressional investigators.
snippet: The testimony seemed to bolster the prosecution’s contention that Roger Stone, an ex-Trump campaign aide, deliberately lied to congressional investigators.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A key witness in the federal criminal trial of Roger J. Stone Jr. testified on Thursday that Mr. Stone had misrepresented him to congressional investigators in 2017 as his intermediary with WikiLeaks even though he had repeatedly urged Mr. Stone to “tell the truth.”

abstract: Mr. Bloomberg is expected to file paperwork this week in at least one state with an early deadline, although an adviser said the former New York mayor had not made a final decision to run.
snippet: Mr. Bloomberg is expected to file paperwork this week in at least one state with an early deadline, although an adviser said the former New York mayor had not made a final decision to run.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg is actively preparing to enter the Democratic presidential primary and is expected to file paperwork this week designating himself as a candidate in at least one state with an early filing deadline, people briefed on Mr. Bloomberg’s plans said.
